cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.SI, cs.AI 

The paper discusses research on health behavior change in the context of human-computer interaction (HCI), which is a subfield of computer science focused on designing and evaluating interactive systems for human use. Therefore, cs.HC is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also discusses the potential of digital technologies for supporting health behavior change, which could fall under cs.CY (computers and society) and cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science). 

The paper mentions the lack of standardized approaches to evaluating user experience, which could fall under cs.SI (social and information networks). 

Finally, the paper suggests opportunities for integrating game design and AI into health behavior change interventions, which could fall under cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
